items.text: SIGNING, STRIPING, AND MARKINGS NOTES (SHEETS AA32-AA34)
SIGNING, STRIPING, AND MARKINGS KEYNOTES (SHEETS AA32-AA34)
THESE PLANS ARE ACCURATE FOR SIGNING, STRIPING, AND MARKINGS ONLY.
SIGNS SHALL BE INSTALLED PER CITY STD. P-8 & P-9, UNLESS OTHERWISE NOTED ON
WORK SHALL BE DONE IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE LATEST EDITION OF THE STATE OF
CALIFORNIA DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION STANDARD PLANS AND
SPECIFICATIONS, SIGN SPECIFICATIONS SHEETS, THE CALIFORNIA MANUAL OF
UNIFORM TRAFFIC CONTROL DEVICES (LATEST EDITION), THE LATEST EDITION OF
THE CITY OF DINUBA STANDARD SPECIFICATIONS AND DRAWINGS, AND THE SPECIAL
ALL EXISTING SIGNS, POSTS, AND EQUIPMENT SHALL BE SALVAGED AND DELIVERED
WHERE SIGNS ARE TO BE INSTALLED, STREET LIGHT POLES SHOULD BE USED, IN
LIEU OF POSTS WHENEVER POSSIBLE. SIGNS INSTALLED ON STREET LIGHT POLES
SHALL BE INSTALLED WITH STAINLESS STEEL BANDING MATERIAL.
STRIPING DESIGNATED TO BE REMOVED SHALL BE REMOVED COMPLETELY AND THE
SURFACE SEALED WITH A "WALKMASTER" OR OWNER-APPROVED EQUIVALENT
SLURRY PRIOR TO RE-STRIPING. ANY VOIDS CREATED BY GRINDING SHALL BE FILLED
USING A TYPE 'II' SLURRY AS DETERMINED BY THE CITY ENGINEER.
ALL EXISTING PAVEMENT DELINEATION IN CONFLICT WITH THE PROPOSED PAVEMENT
DELINEATION SHALL BE REMOVED BY LIGHTLY GRINDING. GRINDING THICKNESS
SHALL BE LIMITED TO ONLY WHAT IS REQUIRED TO REMOVE THE PAVEMENT
DELINEATION FROM THE ROADWAY AND NO MORE.
ALL SIGNS SHALL BE 3M-3930HIP TYPE 'III' & 'IV' SERIES REFLECTIVE SHEETING AND
BE COVERED WITH 1160A PREMIUM OVERLAY ANTI-GRAFFITI FILM OR AVERY
DENNISON T6500 SERIES REFLECTIVE SHEETING AND SHALL BE COVERED WITH
ALL PAVEMENT MARKINGS, CROSSWALK, AND LIMITS LINES IN THE STREET RIGHT OF
WAY SHALL BE THERMOPLASTIC. TRAFFIC STRIPES SHALL BE PAINT (2 COATS WITH
REFLECTIVE GLASS BEADS) UNLESS OTHERWISE DIRECTED BY THE CITY.
CONTRACTOR SHALL REPLACE ANY STRIPING, IN KIND, THAT IS DAMAGED DURING
CONSTRUCTION THAT IS NOT SPECIFIED ON THESE PLANS.
ALL CROSSWALKS SHALL BE 10 FEET WIDE, MEASURED FROM INSIDE EDGE TO INSIDE
EDGE, UNLESS OTHERWISE NOTED ON THE PLANS.
THE CONTRACTOR IS RESPONSIBLE TO RECORD AND DOCUMENT AS NECESSARY
EXISTING STRIPING, PAVEMENT MARKERS, AND MARKINGS AND BLUE DOT MARKERS
FOR FIRE HYDRANTS IN ORDER TO REPLACE THE STRIPING, PAVEMENT MARKERS,
ALL EXISTING SIGNS SHALL BE PROTECTED IN PLACE UNLESS OTHERWISE NOTED ON
THE PLANS. ALL EXISTING SIGNS PROTECTED IN PLACE SHALL BE ADJUSTED TO
FINISHED GRADE SO THAT THE LOWEST SIGN ON THE POST MEETS CLEARANCES
SPECIFIED IN THE CA MUTCD, LATEST EDITION, FOR EACH SIGN TYPE.
THE MINIMUM HEIGHT, MEASURED VERTICALLY FROM THE BOTTOM OF THE LOWEST
SIGN ON A POST, TO THE SIDEWALK, CURB FACE, OR PEDESTRIAN PATH OF TRAVEL
SHALL BE 7'. SIGN INSTALLATIONS SHALL BE IN CONFORMANCE WITH THE CA MUTCD,
CONTRACTOR SHALL MAINTAIN TRAFFIC SIGNS AND TRAFFIC CONTROL WITH
TEMPORARY SIGNAGE. CONTRACTOR SHALL NOT REMOVE ANY TRAFFIC SIGNS THAT
ARE CURRENTLY IN USE WITHOUT A TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT REPLACEMENT IN
EXISTING WET UTILITIES NOT SHOWN FOR CLARITY. SEE SHEETS
